Tags:
  - 959
By: Iamblichus
---
Since it is usual with all men of sound understandings, to call on divinity,
when entering on any philosophic discussion, it is certainly much more
appropriate to do this in the consideration of that philosophy which justly
receives its denomination from the divine Pythagoras. For as it derives its
origin from the Gods, it cannot be apprehended without their inspiring aid.
